<item>
  <title>Sustainable, Resilient, and Just Global Clean Energy Supply Chains</title>
  <link>http://deeppolicylab.github.io/research/clean-energy-supply-chains/</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 




<p><img src="http://deeppolicylab.github.io/research/clean-energy-supply-chains/featured.jpeg" class="img-fluid"></p>
<section id="overview" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="overview">Overview</h2>
<p>This research theme aims at evidence-based analysis to understand the importance of a sustainable and resilient clean energy global supply chains to achieve climate goals. We evaluate the economic costs, carbon mitigation, air quality, and human health benefits achieved by global clean energy supply chains.</p>
</section>
<section id="featured-publications" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="featured-publications">Featured publications</h2>
